          org.netbeans.modules.editor.lib2.document.ContentEdit modifyUndoEdit

          Previous event in the chain of the events that were connected together to be undone/redone at once.

        • inUndo

          boolean inUndo

        • inRedo

          boolean inRedo

        • hasBeenDone2

          boolean hasBeenDone2
          Unfortunately the undo() and redo() methods call writeLock() which the protected final method in AbstractDocument. If somebody calls runAtomic() or runAtomicAsUser() and the exception is thrown in the body of the executed runnables, the document automatically undoes the changes. Unfortunately the undo() in AbstractDocument has the writeLock() call hardcoded which throws IllegalStateException() in this situation. Therefore the BaseDocumentEvent cannot call the super.undo() and has to reimplement the functionality of all the parents. The extWriteLock() and extWriteUnlock() are used instead.

        • mousePoint

          int mousePoint
          Deprecated. 
          Mouse moved point, possibly null. Set from mouse-moved, mouse-entered handlers, so that painting will paint this fold in bold. -1, if mouse is not in the sidebar region. The value is used to compute highlighted portions of the folding outline.

        • mousePointConsumed

          boolean mousePointConsumed
          Deprecated. 
          if true, the CodeFoldingSideBar.mousePoint has been already used to make a PaintInfo active. The flag is tested by CodeFoldingSideBar.traverseForward(org.netbeans.api.editor.fold.Fold, org.netbeans.editor.BaseDocument, org.netbeans.editor.BaseTextUI, int, int, int, java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.Integer, org.netbeans.editor.CodeFoldingSideBar.PaintInfo>) and #traverseBackward after children of the current fold are processed and cleared if the CodeFoldingSideBar.mousePoint falls to the fold area - fields of PaintInfo are set accordingly. It's also used to compute (current) mouseBoundary, so mouse movement does not trigger refreshes eagerly

        • mouseBoundary

          Rectangle mouseBoundary
          Deprecated. 
          Boundaries of the current area under the mouse. Can be eiher the span of the current fold (or part of it), or the span not occupied by any fold. Serves as an optimization for mouse handler, which does not trigger painting (refresh) unless mouse leaves this region.

        • lowestAboveMouse

          int lowestAboveMouse
          Deprecated. 
          Y-end of the nearest fold that ends above the CodeFoldingSideBar.mousePoint. Undefined if mousePoint is null. These two variables are initialized at each level of folds, and help to compute CodeFoldingSideBar.mouseBoundary for the case the mousePointer is OUTSIDE all children (or outside all folds).

        • topmostBelowMouse

          int topmostBelowMouse
          Deprecated. 
          Y-begin of the nearest fold, which starts below the CodeFoldingSideBar.mousePoint. Undefined if mousePoint is null
